headline: Dolphins Q&A: An early look at possible selections with late first-round draft pick
author: David Furones
sentences: If you go chalk in the divisional round, with the 49ers and Cincinnati Bengals losing at the respective top-seeded Green Bay Packers and Tennessee Titans, it’s 26.
Here’s the latest installment of our Miami Dolphins Q&A, where South Florida Sun Sentinel writers David Furones and Omar Kelly answer questions from readers.
If the 49ers advance to the NFC Championship Game, it will drop into the final four selections of the opening round.

— Bob Witmer on Twitter
A: First, let’s clarify that the Dolphins’ place in the first round isn’t set in stone yet.
With the Dolphins owning the San Francisco 49ers’ selection, Miami will select, at best, No.
25, but it could more likely be 26th or fall even further back.
If San Francisco loses and Cincinnati wins, it’s 25.
Q: With the 25th pick of Round 1 … u select whom…?
